SIMPLE: fingered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fingered
<hw>Fin"gered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having leaflets like fingers;
digitate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Marked with figures designating
which finger should be used for each note.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fingerer</ent>⟦br⟧
